{"data": {"date": "2019-03-19", "title": "Microsoft will let PC players test Halo: The Master Chief Collection ahead of release", "article": "<p id=\"aEENia\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242;\">Microsoft today announced that as part of its newly released Halo Insider Program, PC players can&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; color: #e5127d; transition: color 0.1s ease 0s, background-color 0.1s ease 0s, fill 0.1s ease 0s; border-bottom: 1px solid currentcolor;\" href=\"https://www.halowaypoint.com/en-us/community/halo-insider\">sign up to test the upcoming&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Halo: The Master Chief Collection</em></a><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</em>version coming to Windows some time later this year.&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; color: #e5127d; transition: color 0.1s ease 0s, background-color 0.1s ease 0s, fill 0.1s ease 0s; border-bottom: 1px solid currentcolor;\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/3/12/18261723/halo-the-master-chief-collection-pc-release-steam-halo-reach\">Announced last week</a>, the PC port of developer Bungie&rsquo;s&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Halo&nbsp;</em>trilogy, in addition to&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Halo: Reach&nbsp;</em>and the single-player campaign of&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Halo 3: ODST</em>, is coming both to the Microsoft Store and Valve&rsquo;s Steam marketplace. The collection was originally released on Xbox One back in 2014.</p>\n<p id=\"oqlhqZ\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242;\">&ldquo;As a Halo Insider, you&rsquo;ll have the opportunity to regularly provide feedback and insights that help shape and inform current franchise initiatives and the future of Halo,&rdquo; the company&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; color: #e5127d; transition: color 0.1s ease 0s, background-color 0.1s ease 0s, fill 0.1s ease 0s; border-bottom: 1px solid currentcolor;\" href=\"https://www.halowaypoint.com/en-us/community/halo-insider\">says on its dedicated Halo Insider page</a>. &ldquo;You will also be given exclusive opportunities to participate in public flights of in-progress Halo game releases and provide feedback to the development teams.&rdquo;</p>", "id": 2}}